51.0	Karl_Polanyi	Karl Polanyi	Polanyi was born into a Jewish family. His younger brother was chemist and philosopher Michael Polanyi, and was born in Vienna, at the time the capital of the Austro-Hungarian Empire. The son of a prominent member of the bourgeoisie involved in railroads, father Mihály (til 1904 Pollacsek) von Polányi and mother Cecília Wohl, Polanyi was well educated despite the ups and downs of his father's fortune, and he immersed himself in Budapest's active intellectual and artistic scene.	
